{{!
  PROFILE CUSTOM CONTENT SNIPPET

  Adds the Inklings tab content to the character profile page.

  FILE: ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs

  IMPORTANT: This file might be empty or minimal if you don't have other custom profile content.

  STEP 1: Check the file contents
  1. Open your game's ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs
  2. Look at what's in the file:
     - If it's EMPTY or has only comments, use "OPTION A" below
     - If it has existing <div class="tab-content"> with other <div class="tab-pane">, use "OPTION B" below

  Copy ONLY this content:

  ---START COPY HERE---
  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="inklings-tab-pane">
    {{inklings-tab characterId=this.char.id viewerId=this.viewer.id isStaff=this.viewer.isStaff}}
  </div>
  ---END COPY---

  IMPORTANT DETAILS:

  ID MATCHING:
  - The id="inklings-tab-pane" below MUST match the href in profile-custom-tabs.snippet.hbs
  - Do NOT change this value

  PROPERTY NAMES:
  - The component uses: characterId, viewerId, and isStaff
  - These are passed from: this.char.id, this.viewer.id, and this.viewer.isStaff
  - If your profile-custom.hbs uses different property names, update them here
  - Common alternatives: character instead of char, user instead of viewer, etc.
  - Check the rest of your profile-custom.hbs to see what names are used

  ABOUT THE COMPONENT:
  The {{inklings-tab}} component is self-contained - it handles all Inkling operations:
  - View existing Inklings
  - Create new ones
  - Add messages and rolls
  - Submit for staff review
  - Share with other characters/groups
  - All changes save immediately (doesn't use the profile page's save flow)

  IMPORTANT: Before using this snippet, you must complete Step 2 of the README
  (Install Web Portal Components), which includes copying inklings-tab.js to your
  webportal. The web portal integration is entirely optional - if you're running a
  MUSH-only game, you do not need this snippet or the component at all.
}}
